            {
                "text": "Singleton  A single instance is created and shared throughout the application's lifetime. Not correct, because it does not create a new instance every time.  Scoped  A new instance is created per scope (usually per web request in ASP.NET Core). Not correct, because it creates one instance per scope, not per request.  Transient  A new instance is created every time the service is requested. Correct answer, because this matches the question exactly.  Persistent  This is not a standard service lifetime in ASP.NET Core Dependency Injection. Irrelevant option.",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "text": "life time - singleton request - transient",
